---
title: "Memory Palace — Query-Time Projection (Critical Path)"
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor User
    participant Router as Query Router
    participant Cache as Projection Cache
    participant FTS as FTS5 Index
    participant Graph as Relationship Graph
    participant Store as Claim Store (SQLite)
    participant Assembler as Context Assembler
    participant LLM as LLM Reasoning
    participant Writeback as Writeback Pipeline

    Note over User,Writeback: ── FAST PATH (80% of queries) ──

    User ->> Router: "What's the current status of Project X?"
    Router ->> Cache: Read L0 global summary (~2K tokens)
    Cache -->> Router: L0 context (entity registry, hot topics, state)

    Router ->> Router: Does L0 contain sufficient signal?
    alt L0 sufficient (simple factual query)
        Router ->> Assembler: L0 context only
        Assembler ->> LLM: System prompt + L0 (single read, ~2K tokens)
        LLM -->> User: Answer (no file reads in critical path)
    end

    Note over User,Writeback: ── STANDARD PATH (15% of queries) ──

    Router ->> Cache: Check L1 cache for cluster "Project X"
    alt L1 cache hit
        Cache -->> Router: L1 cluster summary (~1-2K tokens)
    else L1 cache miss
        Router ->> FTS: keyword search "Project X status"
        FTS -->> Router: ranked claim_ids
        Router ->> Store: Fetch claims + entity context
        Store -->> Router: claim rows + entity metadata
        Router ->> Cache: Write L1 cache (scope_key: cluster:project_x)
    end

    Router ->> Assembler: L0 + L1 cluster context
    Assembler ->> Assembler: Token budget check (trim by priority × recency × confidence)
    Assembler ->> LLM: System prompt + L0 + L1 (~4-6K tokens)
    LLM -->> User: Answer with citations

    Note over User,Writeback: ── DEEP PATH (5% of queries) ──

    User ->> Router: "Compare claim A vs claim B across all sources, noting contradictions"
    Router ->> Cache: Read L0
    Router ->> FTS: search "claim A" + "claim B"
    FTS -->> Router: claim_ids for both
    Router ->> Graph: Traverse from entities A, B — find shared edges, contradictions
    Graph -->> Router: subgraph (entities, claims, relationships, contradictions)
    Router ->> Store: Fetch full claim details + source spans (L2)
    Store -->> Router: detailed claim rows + raw source excerpts
    Router ->> Assembler: L0 + L1 + L2 source excerpts
    Assembler ->> Assembler: Token budget enforcement
    Assembler ->> LLM: Full context (~8-12K tokens)
    LLM -->> User: Detailed comparative analysis

    Note over User,Writeback: ── WRITEBACK (conditional) ──

    LLM ->> LLM: Is this answer worth persisting?
    alt Answer contains novel synthesis
        LLM ->> Writeback: New claims extracted from answer
        Writeback ->> Store: INSERT claims (source_type: "synthesis")
        Writeback ->> Cache: Invalidate affected L0/L1 caches
        Note over Writeback: L0 regeneration is async (next ingest cycle or immediate if critical)
    end
